<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4580720>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "FIGURE 34. Jassa valida (Dana, 1853). Variation in thumb length relative to body length in a single population of males at Radio Island, Beaufort, North Carolina, 31 March 1975, McGovern, coll., IZ 1975-93 (CMN). Linear regression assumptions passed for the adult major form and minor form males. Linear regression statistics: Major form, thumb length = -0.704 + 0.252 body length, r2 = 0.802, n = 8; minor form, thumb length = -0.317 + 0.123 body length, r2 = 0.713, n = 12." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4580720/files/figure.png" .
